Front facade of the American Museum of Natural History.
Jan. 1925
Central Park West 79th - 80th St.
title: Manhattan: Central Park South - 77th Street

text:
Entrance Driveway for West Drive traffic entering Central Park at the West 79th Street entrance (the Old Hunters' Gate). The older part of the Natural History Museum, near 77th Street, is shown in the background.

May 17, 1933.

P.L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Drives.

text:
(1)
Central Park: The Lake, view northwest towards 79th Street, showing the Natural History Museum in Manhattan Square, 79th to 81st Streets, and the Hotel Beresford on the N.W. corner of 81st Street and Central Park West.
Beyond the little bridge there is a little bay between the automobile drive and Central Park West.
May 17, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, another view.
May 17, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
